<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/TribeAssertion/53> rdfs:label "Tribe Assertion: #53" ;
	a dprr:TribeAssertion ;
	dprr:isUncertain true ;
	dprr:isAboutPerson <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/Person/2536> ;
	dprr:hasTribe <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/Tribe/16> ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySource <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNotes "As the Valerii Messallae who were consules suffecti, one in 32 (255) and the other, Corvinus, in 31 (261) were hardly senior enough to take first place in the senatorial committee listed in the SC de Aphrodisiensibus (in 39, not 35, as in MRR 2.406; Sherk, RDGE 170ff.; see J. M. Reynolds, Aphrodisias and Rome 54-91, esp. 67-68), Badian's suggestion (reported by Reynolds, ibid. 67) that the Messalla who is placed first was the consul of 53 becomes very attractive. If it is correct, the consul's filiation is M. f. and his tribe is Lem. " ;
	dprr:hasID 53 .
